      <h2>Miele dishwasher repair, common questions</h2>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>What does F11 mean?</summary>
        <p>Drainage fault. Filter combination blocked (free cleanup, fixes 50%), drain pump impeller broken ($185-$285), non-return valve jammed (free cleanup), drain hose kinked. Full decoder table above. Power cycle clears transient F11; persistent F11 needs service.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>F24, dishes coming out cold</summary>
        <p>Heater relay error. Relay on control board (most common), wiring harness, or heating element open-circuit. Heating element tests 20-30 ohms good. On G 7000 the heater relay is board-mounted = control board replacement $580-$820 if relay is the cause. Element alone $285-$420.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>F52 after a cycle</summary>
        <p>Excess foam. Wrong detergent, regular dish soap, combi tablets without Combi Tablet Program activated, or AutoDos + manual detergent double-dose. Fix: power cycle, activate Combi Tablet Program if using tablets, don't combine AutoDos with manual. No parts needed.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>F79, Miele won't start</summary>
        <p>Electrical supply fault. In LA luxury kitchens, often Lutron Caseta dimmer on shared or adjacent circuit interferes with Miele control. Fixes: confirm dedicated 20A circuit, move/remove dimmer, install line filter. Once isolated, F79 doesn't recur.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>F600 or F601 on my G 7000 AutoDos</summary>
        <p>AutoDos dispensing fault. Reseat PowerDisk (40% resolve free), replace near-empty PowerDisk, clean dispensing outlet, test AutoDos motor ($245-$340). We diagnose before ordering.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How much does Miele dishwasher repair cost?</summary>
        <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Common: drain pump $185-$285, circulation pump $385-$540, AquaStop valve $245-$345, heater $285-$420, control board $580-$820. Full pricing table above.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How fast can you come out?</summary>
        <p>Same-day for calls before 1 PM weekday inside coverage. Malibu, Hidden Hills, Pacific Palisades get next-morning priority. For a leaking dishwasher with AquaStop triggered, call and tell us, we rearrange routing.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Is Miele Professional the same as the Miele residential dishwashers you service?</summary>
        <p>No, different product scope, different service path. Miele Professional is Miele's commercial foodservice division (commercial dishwashers, commercial laundry, commercial lab + medical equipment). If you have a Miele commercial dishwasher at a restaurant, dental office, veterinary clinic, or laboratory with "Miele Professional" branding, that unit goes through the Miele Professional factory-authorized commercial service network. Our team services the Miele residential dishwasher line, G 5000 Discovery, G 7000 AutoDos, Futura, integrated panel-ready, which shares the Miele & Cie. KG parent (Gütersloh) but uses a distinct residential service path with residential parts channels and residential warranty routing.</p>
      </details>
